==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wn-li
<hw>W⟦ecir⟧n"-li`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chin.
<ets>w⟦ecir⟧n li</ets>.]</ety> <def>The higher literary idiom of
Chinese, that of the canonical books and of all composition pretending
to literary standing. It employs a classical or academic diction, and a
more condensed and sententious style than Mandarin, and differs also in
the doubling and arrangement of words.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

